Ask HN: Why are physics and math majors omnipresent in diverse research domains?
text:
When I search grad student profiles in CS and financial research groups, I often find that there are students who did their undergrads or even masters in mathematics or physics.

Although they are in minority among a huge number of CS grads, but that is not the point. I don't find that many biology or chemistry majors being everywhere in such an interdisciplinary manner.

What makes physics and math graduates so strong to work in wide variety of domains? What is the skillset they possess?

Ask HN: How to find clients in the US?
text: I’m an experienced dev and am now in the process of starting an agency, or venturing out on my own as a contractor. I’m based in Eastern Europe but my goal is to find US clients to work with, mainly because of potentially more interesting projects, and higher pay. What do you think would be the best route to achieve this? Does good work speak for itself, should I incorporate in the US as well, perhaps fly-in and make connections in person, anything else that could help?

ADP May have been HACKED
text:
I am still not 100% certain about what's going on, but this is the second pay period in a row where my Routing# and Account# have been updated on ADP's website without my consent. Luckily I caught it the first time, and basically just made it out to be a temporary glitch. Now I know something fishy is going on now that it's been the second pay period in a row where my direct deposit info has been updated to the SAME ACCOUNT as last time.

This is the (alleged) hacker's account info where my most recent paycheck was deposited today:

Bank of America Routing#: 121000358 Account#: 325026596833
